Detailed Description

Contains definitions/structures used in the Covered utility.

Author:
Trevor Williams (trevorw@charter.net)
Date:
11/27/2001
This file is included by all files within Covered. All defines, macros, structures, enums, and typedefs in the tool are specified in this file.

Define Documentation

#define COVERED_HEADER   "\nCovered %s -- Verilog Code Coverage Utility\nWritten by Trevor Williams (trevorw@charter.net)\nFreely distributable under the GPL license\n", COVERED_VERSION
 

This contains the header information specified when executing this tool.

#define COVERED_VERSION   VERSION
 

Specifies current version of the Covered utility.

#define DFLT_OUTPUT_DB   "cov.db"
 

Default database filename if not specified on command-line.

#define EXPR_COMB_MISSED (  x   ) 
 

Value:

(EXPR_IS_MEASURABLE( x ) & \
                                    ~expression_is_static_only( x ) & \
                                    (~SUPPL_WAS_TRUE( x->suppl ) | ~SUPPL_WAS_FALSE( x->suppl )))
Returns a value of 1 if the specified expression was measurable for combinational coverage but not fully covered during simulation.

#define EXPR_IS_MEASURABLE (  x   ) 
 

Value:

(((SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) != EXP_OP_STATIC) && \
                                     (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) != EXP_OP_LAST) && \
                                     (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) != EXP_OP_LIST) && \
                                     (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) != EXP_OP_COND_SEL) && \
                                     (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) != EXP_OP_CASE) && \
                                     (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) != EXP_OP_CASEX) && \
                                     (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) != EXP_OP_CASEZ) && \
                                     (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) != EXP_OP_DEFAULT) && \
                                     (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) != EXP_OP_PARAM) && \
                                     (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) != EXP_OP_PARAM_SBIT) && \
                                     (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) != EXP_OP_PARAM_MBIT) && \
                                     (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) != EXP_OP_DELAY) && \
                                     !((SUPPL_IS_ROOT( x->suppl ) == 0) && \
                                       ((SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) == EXP_OP_SIG) || \
                                        (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) == EXP_OP_SBIT_SEL) || \
                                        (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) == EXP_OP_MBIT_SEL)) && \
                                       (SUPPL_OP( x->parent->expr->suppl ) != EXP_OP_COND))) ? 1 : 0)
Returns a value of 1 if the specified expression is considered to be measurable.

#define EXPR_IS_STATIC (  x   ) 
 

Value:

((SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) == EXP_OP_STATIC)     || \
                                  (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) == EXP_OP_PARAM)      || \
                                  (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) == EXP_OP_PARAM_SBIT) || \
                                  (SUPPL_OP( x->suppl ) == EXP_OP_PARAM_MBIT))
Returns a value of TRUE if the specified expression is a STATIC, PARAM, PARAM_SBIT or PARAM_MBIT operation type.

typedef unsigned int control
 

A control is a 32-bit value that is subdivided into the following parts:
Bits Field Description
5:0 See SUPPL_LSB_OP
6 See SUPPL_LSB_SWAPPED
7 See SUPPL_LSB_ROOT
8 See SUPPL_LSB_EXECUTED
9 See SUPPL_LSB_STMT_HEAD
10 See SUPPL_LSB_STMT_STOP
11 See SUPPL_LSB_STMT_CONTINUOUS
12 See SUPPL_LSB_FALSE
13 See SUPPL_LSB_TRUE
14 See SUPPL_LSB_LEFT_CHANGED
15 See SUPPL_LSB_RIGHT_CHANGED
16 See SUPPL_LSB_EVAL_00
17 See SUPPL_LSB_EVAL_01
18 See SUPPL_LSB_EVAL_10
19 See SUPPL_LSB_EVAL_11
20 See SUPPL_LSB_EVAL_T
21 See SUPPL_LSB_EVAL_F
22 See SUPPL_LSB_COMB_CNTD
23 See SUPPL_LSB_STMT_CONNECTED
24 See SUPPL_LSB_STMT_ADDED
31:25 Reserved

typedef unsigned int nibble
 

A nibble is a 32-bit value that is subdivided into the following parts:
Bits Field Description
7:0 Current 4-state value for bits 3-0
11:8 Indicator if associated bit was toggled from 0->1
15:12 Indicator if associated bit was toggled from 1->0
19:16 Indicator if associated bit has been previously assigned this timestep
21:20 Indicates original value type (HEXIDECIMAL, OCTAL, BINARY, DECIMAL)
23:22 General purpose bits
27:24 Indicator if associated bit was set to a value of 0 (FALSE)
31:28 Indicator if associated bit was set to a value of 1 (TRUE)
